text:
Broadway, west side, from Thames Street to Liberty Street, showing the Boreel Building later replaced by the Twenty-one story United States Reality Building, on the left is a corner of the Old Trinity Building.

1890-1900

Broadway, west side, south from Thames Street. The view shows Trinity Church and Grounds. On the extreme right, is shown the old Trinity Building, the executive headquarters of this old church.

About 1895.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
